```
2. In the newly created `app/Http/Middleware/CheckToken.php` file, add the following code:


```php
use Closure;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Auth;

class CheckToken
{
 public function handle(Request $request, Closure $next)
 {
 if (Auth::check()) {
 $request->merge(['customer\_id' => Auth::id()]);
 }

 return $next($request);
 }
}
```
3. In the `app/Http/Kernel.php` file, add the `CheckToken` middleware to the `$middleware` array:


